Dear All,

I am pleased to announce the availability of my programs: WinOcaml and
WinCoq, which are Window95 graphic interface for Ocaml and Coq. 

WinOcaml integrates the Ocaml command interpreter with a Multiple
file editor and a Ocaml source code browser.

WinOcaml integrates the Coq command interpreter with a Multiple file
editor and a Coq source code browser.

Main features of these programs are: 

-- Execution from editor by RETURN
-- Execution of selected region
-- Stepwise execution
-- Source code brouwser
-- Multiple file editor
-- Dynamicly display line and column number
-- Search and replace 
-- Maintain a recent file list for quick open
-- Automatically display hints for buttons when mouse is moved over them

WinOcaml and WinCoq can be download from 
    http://www.dmi.ens.fr/~gang/ 


Cheers.

Gang Chen




